stylometry: Decision trees are important because they help managers to choose the optimal course of action when a situation has alternative/multiple courses of action with unknown results stemming from the each alternative choice. They are used by they measure all the possible results and then compare them to each other and then spit out the one that fits your situation the best. An example how you could use one is if you were trying to decide which city in Ohio to open a new chain of your restaurant  in. You could get the data from each one of those cities based on simular restaurants or on the eating out characteristics of the people in each city. Then you put all the information you gathered into the tree and it will give you the statistically best city for you to choose.
